\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Tightness of the information envelope on approximately balanced binary pairs (Proposition~\ref {prop:tight}). Curve: the exact ratio $\sqrt  {I(r)/2}\,/\,(|r|/2)$; dashes: the leading correction $1+r^2/12$; points: per-lag plug-in ratios $\sqrt  {\hat  I/2}\,/\,(|\hat  r|/2)$ for the five approximately balanced battery series ($|\hat  \pi -\tfrac  12|<.035$, $|r|>.05$). A consistency illustration rather than an independent test ($\hat  I$ and $\hat  r$ derive from the same pooled lag table): the plug-in points ride the predicted curve across the full correlation range. (The ratio to the exact \emph  {value} $\setbox \z@ \hbox {\mathsurround \z@ $\textstyle V$}\mathaccent "0362{V}_1$ lifts above this curve at small $r$ for the mildly imbalanced series --- that is Theorem~\ref {thm:hinge}'s threshold, not envelope slack; see Fig.~\ref {fig:trichotomy}.)}}{13}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:tightness}{{2}{13}{Tightness of the information envelope on approximately balanced binary pairs (Proposition~\ref {prop:tight}). Curve: the exact ratio $\sqrt {I(r)/2}\,/\,(|r|/2)$; dashes: the leading correction $1+r^2/12$; points: per-lag plug-in ratios $\sqrt {\hat I/2}\,/\,(|\hat r|/2)$ for the five approximately balanced battery series ($|\hat \pi -\tfrac 12|<.035$, $|r|>.05$). A consistency illustration rather than an independent test ($\hat I$ and $\hat r$ derive from the same pooled lag table): the plug-in points ride the predicted curve across the full correlation range. (The ratio to the exact \emph {value} $\widehat V_1$ lifts above this curve at small $r$ for the mildly imbalanced series --- that is Theorem~\ref {thm:hinge}'s threshold, not envelope slack; see Fig.~\ref {fig:trichotomy}.)}{figure.2}{}}
