\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces The battery at a glance. Dots: maximum history-class gain over the exact single-sample value; grey bars: the model-calibrated interval $[\hat  g-\varepsilon _{\mathrm  {over}},\hat  g+\varepsilon _{\mathrm  {under}}]$; ticks: the moving-block one-sided bounds at fixed $D^*$ (upper, teal) and with in-replicate lag selection (lower, orange); dotted line: the registered practical floor. Only seismic separates decisively from both zero and the floor; the i.i.d.\ null's positive selection-aware tick is the empirical winner's-curse floor; whale's wide bar is the short-series noise the verdict language respects. Where $\varepsilon _{\mathrm  {under}}<0$ (whale, i.i.d.) the bias-corrected upper endpoint $U_2$ sits \emph  {below} the point estimate --- the estimator is upward-biased there, and the bound says so.}}{14}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:battery}{{3}{14}{The battery at a glance. Dots: maximum history-class gain over the exact single-sample value; grey bars: the model-calibrated interval $[\hat g-\varepsilon _{\mathrm {over}},\hat g+\varepsilon _{\mathrm {under}}]$; ticks: the moving-block one-sided bounds at fixed $D^*$ (upper, teal) and with in-replicate lag selection (lower, orange); dotted line: the registered practical floor. Only seismic separates decisively from both zero and the floor; the i.i.d.\ null's positive selection-aware tick is the empirical winner's-curse floor; whale's wide bar is the short-series noise the verdict language respects. Where $\varepsilon _{\mathrm {under}}<0$ (whale, i.i.d.) the bias-corrected upper endpoint $U_2$ sits \emph {below} the point estimate --- the estimator is upward-biased there, and the bound says so}{figure.3}{}}
